  "content": "# apps use useSelectedDrive to access drive state and filter nodes\n\nApps (drive editors) use the `useSelectedDrive()` hook to access the drive document, then filter nodes to display specific document types:\n\n```typescript\nconst [document] = useSelectedDrive();\n\n// Get file nodes from the drive\nconst fileNodes = document?.state.global.nodes.filter(\n  (node) => node.kind === \"file\"\n) || [];\n\n// Filter by document type\nconst documentModels = fileNodes.filter(\n  (node) => node.documentType === \"powerhouse/document-model\"\n);\n```\n\nReference implementation: `packages/vetra/editors/vetra-drive-app/`.\n\nSince [[document model vs document editor vs app serves different purposes]], apps manage collections while editors handle individual documents.\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[editor patterns]]\n- [[model-editor wiring]]",
